<div id="PJA12d287" class="doc letter">

<h2>From the Duc de La Vauguyon</h2>

<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationRight">La haye ce 2 avril 1782</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Je me proposois Monsieur daller passer quelques jours a amsterdam a la fin de Cette Semaine, mais je suis absolument oblig de rester icy et jaurai lhonneur de vous en dire Les raisons. Je Desirerois bien cependant mentretenir avec vous; et je vous prierois de venir a La haye si vous netes pas indispensablement retenu a amsterdam.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA12d288n1" id="PJA12d288n1-ptr">1</a></p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="salute">Receves Monsieur une nouvelle assurance Des Sentiments Inviolables dattachement et de consideration avec les quels jay Lhonneur detre Votre tres humble et tres obeissant serviteur</p>
<p class="signed">Le Duc De La vauguyon</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="PJA12d288" class="trans letter">

 <h2>The Duc de La Vauguyon to John Adams: A Translation</h2>
 
<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationRight">The Hague, 2 April 1782</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I had proposed, sir, to spend a few days in Amsterdam at the end of this week, but I am absolutely obliged to remain here and will have the honor of informing you of the reasons. In the meantime, I want very much to speak with you and pray that you would come to The Hague unless you are indispensibly detained at Amsterdam.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA12d288n1" id="PJA12d288n1-ptr">1</a></p>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="ADMS-06-12-02-pb-0381">[381]</span>
<div class="closer">
<p class="salute">Receive, sir, a new assurance of the inviolable sentiments of attachment and consideration with which I have the honor of being your very humble and very obedient servant.</p>
<p class="signed">Le Duc De La vauguyon</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="PJA12d288sn1">
<p>
<span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>).</span>
</p>
</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA12d288n1-ptr" id="PJA12d288n1">1</a>
<p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> went to The Hague on the morning of 4 April and returned on the 6th (Dumas to Robert R. Livingston, 4 April, <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Francis Wharton, ed., &lt;i&gt;The Revolutionary Diplomatic Correspondence of the United States&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 1889; 6 vols. ]">Wharton, ed., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Dipl. Corr. Amer. Rev.</span></span>, 5:292293).</p>
</div>
